---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Accounting Services"
  description="Tax Doctor offers a full accounting service tailored to your business needs, including financial statements, company annual returns, payroll and more."
  keywords="accounting, financial statements, cipc, company returns, payroll, sars, bookkeeping, johannesburg"
>
  <div class="section">
    <h2>Accounting</h2>
    <img class="image-section" alt="Accounting" src="/images/Services/taxbalance.jpg" />
    <p>We offer a full accounting service which can be tailored to your needs and includes the following:</p>
    <ul class="alt">
      <li>Annual financial statements</li>
      <li>Accounting Officer services</li>
      <li>Tax services</li>
      <li>Company annual returns to CIPC</li>
      <li>CC to Pty conversions</li>
      <li>New company formations</li>
      <li>Meeting all statutory requirements</li>
      <li>Submission of annual Workmens Compensation returns</li>
      <li>Payroll</li>
      <li>WCA registrations and annual submissions</li>
      <li>UIF Services</li>
      <li>Audits e.g. SARS and company</li>
      <li>General Business Advice</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="minisection">
      <b>Financial Statements</b> include the following:
      <ul class="alt">
        <img class="image-section" alt="Tax Reporting" src="/images/Services/taxreports.jpg" />
        <li>Directors and Accounting Officer / Auditor reports</li>
        <li>Balance sheet</li>
        <li>Income statement (Profit and Loss)</li>
        <li>Fixed assets schedule</li>
        <li>Cashflow projections</li>
        <li>Notes to the balance sheet and income statement</li>
      </ul>
      <p>There are many reasons why people need financial statements, for example:</p>
      <ul class="alt">
        <li>Submission to SARS (IT14)</li>
        <li>Management reporting on profit and loss, customers/suppliers age analysis, reconciliations, etc.</li>
        <li>Bank loans</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We can provide statements in Excel and/or Quickbooks.</p>
    </div>

    <b>CIPC Services</b>
    <ul class="alt">
      <li>New company registrations, amendments and annual submissions</li>
      <li>Close Corporation amendments and annual submissions</li>
      <li>CC De-registration</li>
      <li>CC Reinstatements</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Layout>
